#25524
Bottom of the stairs~
You pause at the base of a massive set of steps. Before you the 
clock tower rises high into the sky, a seemingly endless expanse 
of glass and stone. Behind you sirens sounds loud and clear in the 
cool air. Police cars line the street in front, and pedestrians and 
officers move in what seems like an intricate dance of movements 
in and out of the building itself. High above the hand of the clock 
tower moves ever closer to striking the hour, loud enough to drown 
out the wailing sirens and general noise of the city to announce 
the passage of time.
