#25538
Outside on a ledge~
A chill wind slides through your clothing. The suns light providing 
practically no warmth at all. Huge, life-size statues rest on huge 
stone blocks in front of you. Each is stretched out in a different pose, 
wings spread and facing outwards they seem to scream a silent 
protest to the world. Surrounding the tower are the huge skyscraper 
buildings of the city. You peek over the edge to the street far below 
and see the cars whizzing past the station looking like tiny ants 
from this distance. Another chill wind blows through your clothes 
and you sincerely consider going back inside.
